  "text": "i.e., it is a weighted running average of {x i (r + 1)} k r=0 . Such an auxiliary sequence is referred to as primal recovery procedure and it is often used in dual decomposition methods, since it has better convergence properties compared to {x i (k)} k\u22650 [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] .",
